    "Among open-source alternatives, Meta's LLaMa2 has 70 billion parameters [11].",
    "The utility of LLMs has led to their adoption in biomedical research and application, and some LLMs have been customized or tuned specifically for medical text.",
    "In the following sections, we provide an overview of the development and use of LLMs, specifically generative ones, within biomedical NLP.",
    "The rest of this chapter is organized as follows: in section 2, we outline the training of biomedical LLMs, currently available biomedical LLMs, and their uses; in sections 3 to 5, we highlight the use of LLMs for distinct types of medical textsliterature, electronic health records (EHRs), and social media, respectively; in section 6, we discuss topics such as bias, reproducibility, and privacy; and we conclude the chapter in section 7 by outlining key limitations and future directions for medical LLMs.",
    "Adapting LLMs for the Medical Domain Training Medical LLMsAlthough generic LLMs like ChatGPT 1 and GPT-4 [12] have demonstrated their robustness in diverse contexts, their performance on medical texts is often suboptimal [13,14], perhaps due to insufficient medical domain-specific training data [15,16]."
